Taken together, there is a profound difference in the taxes paid by poor families in Southwest versus the Northeast. Whereas the Jones family faces a net tax burden of several hundred dollars in many Southwestern states, that same family would receive a tax refund of several hundred dollars in many Northeastern states, thanks to generous refundable tax credits. Moving from one state to another could save families up to $1,000
